President Donald J. Trump and Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas met at the White House to discuss Middle East peace and strengthen US-Palestinian relations. They both expressed commitment to achieving a genuine and lasting peace between Israelis and Palestinians through direct negotiations. President Trump appreciated President Abbas' support for a negotiated settlement. They agreed that a solution cannot be imposed by any party and discussed creating a conducive climate for progress. They also reaffirmed their determination to combat violence and terrorism, emphasizing the importance of preventing inflammatory rhetoric and stopping incitement. President Trump raised concerns about payments to Palestinian prisoners and their families. Additionally, they discussed the importance of enabling economic growth in the West Bank and Gaza Strip. The two leaders agreed to continue close consultations.